#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.Generator.f:69
msgid "An example from Glantz[1], pp 47-40:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.Generator.f:71
msgid ""
"Two groups, children of diabetics (25 people) and children from people "
"without diabetes (25 controls). Fasting blood glucose was measured, case "
"group had a mean value of 86.1, controls had a mean value of 82.2. Standard "
"deviations were 2.09 and 2.49 respectively. Are these data consistent with "
"the null hypothesis that the parents diabetic status does not affect their "
"children's blood glucose levels? Calculating the F statistic from the data "
"gives a value of 36.01."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
